ass="qx-element-call-to-action_wrapper qx-animation-toggle classic-mode" > <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_content"> <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_subtitle"> <h2> The 6 Essentials, the Beefmaster breed was built on! </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_description"> <span class="fontstyle0">The Six Essentials are what differentiates Beefmasters from all other beef breeds.</span> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-bi3js" class="qx-column qx-d-sm-none qx-d-lg-flex qx-d-md-flex qx-d-xs-none qx-d-none" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='qx-section-ntvya' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/poster/beeffuture.png > <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-yj7vj' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div id="qx-column-d542z" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="fertility" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/fertility.jpg' alt='images/Siteimages/Essentials/fertility.jpg' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Fertility </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;">Females should be feminine, early maturing, early breeding, and raise a calf annually. Calving ease and excellent mothering ability are paramount. Maternal productivity and efficiency are the primary purpose and focus of the breed.</div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-1mutz" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="disposition" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><noscript><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition.jpg' alt='Beefmaster Disposition' class='' /></noscript><picture><source data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_562.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 562w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_470.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 470w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_393.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 393w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_329.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 329w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Beefmaster Disposition' class=' lazyload blur-up' type='image/webp'/><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_562.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 562w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_470.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 470w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_393.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 393w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/disposition_329.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 329w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Beefmaster Disposition' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-lowsrc='data:;base64,'/></picture></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Disposition </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Beefmasters should be relatively docile, easy to handle, and responsive. Gentle cattle have higher performance and save money in labor costs for owners and carcass yield for processors. Cattle with a nervous or mean disposition are problematic and should be culled and/or avoided in breeding programs<br /><br /></span></div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='qx-section-c72hy' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/poster/beeffuture.png > <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-igm0u' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div id="qx-column-8ehjp" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="weight" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/weight.jpg' alt='Beefmaster Weight' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Weight </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Beefmaster calves should be moderate weight and easy calving at birth then show good growth and heavy weight relative to age and environment as compared to other cattle. They should gain well in all phases of development. Moderation of mature size, especially relative to environment, is desirable and will yield a more efficient animal with better weaning weights.<br /></span></div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-ysh1u" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="milk" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/milkproduction.jpg' alt='Beefmaster Milk Production' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Milk Production </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;"><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">After genetics, this is the single most important factor in calf weight. Beefmaster females should be heavy, but not excessive in milk production. Udder design is critical to longevity as a productive replacement female. The udder should show ample capacity with a high attachment that extends level and forward in the front and upward in the rear.<br /></span></div></div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='qx-section-bd588' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/poster/beeffuture.png > <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-8jtil' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div id="qx-column-e2g2o" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="confirmation" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/confirmation.jpg' alt='Beefmaster Confirmation' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Confirmation </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">This refers to the visual appraisal of a live animal with regard to carcass merit. We select for long, trim, well-muscled bulls, and smooth, feminine cows that meet industry demands.<br /></span></div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-9yk4e" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="hardiness" class="qx-element qx-element-blurb-v2" > <div class="qx-element-blurb_wrapper qx-align-items-center position-center"> <figure class="qx-element-blurb__media qx-display-inline-block type-image"><noscript><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness.jpg' alt='Beefmaster Hardiness' class='' /></noscript><picture><source data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_556.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 556w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_465.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 465w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_389.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 389w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_325.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 325w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Beefmaster Hardiness' class=' lazyload blur-up' type='image/webp'/><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_556.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 556w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_465.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 465w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_389.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 389w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Essentials/hardiness_325.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Essentials 325w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Beefmaster Hardiness' class=' lazyload blur-up' data-lowsrc='data:;base64,'/></picture></figure> <div class="qx-element-blurb__content qx-width-1-1" data="center"> <div class="qx-element-blurb__title"> <h2> Hardiness </h2> </div> <div class="qx-element-blurb__body"> <div style="text-align: center;"><div style="text-align: center;"><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Beefmasters are designed to be very hardy cattle, excellent foragers, and travel well. They should be able to withstand a wide range of temperatures and humidity. Beefmasters display natural resistance to insects and parasites. They are exceptionally healthy, trouble-free cattle.<br /></span></div></div></div></div> </div> </div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='history' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/Siteimages/Sections/Beefmaster4.jpg > <div class="history-background-overlay qx-background-overlay" ></div> <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-p4ozz' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div id="qx-column-f49uw" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="history-background" class="qx-element qx-element-call-to-action-v2" qx-scrollspy="cls:qx-animation-scale-down;repeat:ture;delay:300ms" > <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_wrapper qx-animation-toggle classic-mode" > <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_content qx-justify-content-start qx-d-flex qx-flex-column"> <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_subtitle"> <h2> HISTORY </h2> </div> </div> </div> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-iwikz" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2" > Beginning in the early 1930s, Tom Lasater, the breed&rsquo;s founder, developed Beefmasters from a systematic crossing of Hereford, Shorthorn and Brahman cattle. </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='qx-section-x7vec' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bgset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/poster/beeffuturesmall_300.png&dirs=poster 300w' data-sizes='auto' > <div class="qx-section-x7vec-background-overlay qx-background-overlay" ></div> <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-b9nw0' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div id="qx-column-qzg6p" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-f6jye" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2 qx-d-sm-none qx-d-lg-block qx-d-md-block qx-d-xs-none qx-d-none" > <div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br />Beefmasters are a composite breed made up of roughly one-half Bos Taurus (Hereford and Shorthorn) and one-half Bos Indicus (Nelore from Brasil, Gir & Guzerat from India). <br /><br />Lasater&rsquo;s purpose was to develop cattle that were more productive than existing breeds; cattle that would produce and make money during economically hard times in the harsh environment of South Texas. Intense selection for economically important traits over the last 80 years has resulted in a homozygous beef breed that has locked in the explosive growth potential of a hybrid. <br /><br />The breed was developed on what has become known as the Six Essentials - <strong>Weight, Conformation, Milk Production, Fertility, Hardiness, and Disposition</strong>. These essentials became the economic strength of Beefmasters and have made them favorites with those who depend on cattle for a living. <br /><br />Beefmasters are the only beef breed specifically developed to excel in these important economic traits. Beefmaster cattle are the first American composite breed (combination of three or more breeds). <br /></span></div> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-ki7h3" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2 qx-d-lg-none qx-d-sm-block qx-d-xs-block qx-d-md-none qx-d-block" > <div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br />Beginning in the early 1930s, Tom Lasater, the breed&rsquo;s founder, developed Beefmasters from a systematic crossing of Hereford, Shorthorn and Brahman cattle.<br />Beefmasters are a composite breed made up of roughly one-half Bos Taurus (Hereford and Shorthorn) and one-half Bos Indicus (Nelore from Brasil, Gir & Guzerat from India). Lasater&rsquo;s purpose was to develop cattle that were more productive than existing breeds; cattle that would produce and make money during economically hard times in the harsh environment of South Texas. Intense selection for economically important traits over the last 80 years has resulted in a homozygous beef breed that has locked in the explosive growth potential of a hybrid.<br />The breed was developed on what has become known as the Six Essentials - Weight, Conformation, Milk Production, Fertility, Hardiness, and Disposition. These essentials became the economic strength of Beefmasters and have made them favorites with those who depend on cattle for a living. Beefmasters are the only beef breed specifically developed to excel in these important economic traits. Beefmaster cattle are the first American composite breed (combination of three or more breeds).&nbsp;<br /></span></div> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-r2iga" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-image-on82l" class="qx-element qx-element-image-v2" > <img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Content/tomlasater.jpg' alt='Tom Lasater' class='qx-img-fluid lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /> <figcaption class="qx-figure-caption">Photography by Stewart M. Green</figcaption> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-6byhi" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2" > <span style="font-size: 12pt;">Tom Lasater applied scales and regular measurements to compare top performers within the herd and eliminate males and females that did not meet his expected Six Essentials. The Foundation Herd excelled in confirming top performers in all areas. Tom Lasater closed his herd in 1937, and no outside genetics have been introduced into the Foundation Herd since that time. The Foundation Herd was moved to Matheson, Colorado, from South Texas in 1948 and was accepted by USDA as &ldquo;Beefmaster&rdquo; in 1954. </span> </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <div id='qx-section-2b21n' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/Siteimages/Sections/Beefmaster11.jpg > <div class="qx-section-2b21n-background-overlay qx-background-overlay" ></div> <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-vxiiy' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row qx-row-align-center' > <div id="qx-column-d2uw7" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-xck3y" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2" qx-scrollspy="cls:qx-animation-scale-down;delay:" > THE MOST PROFITABLE BREED OF CATTLE IN THE WORLD </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></div> <section id='qx-section-tetx4' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg' > <div class="qx-section-tetx4-background-overlay qx-background-overlay lazyload lazyload-bg blur-up" data-bgset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/poster/beeffuturesmall_300.png&dirs=poster 300w' data-sizes='auto'></div> <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-qbn94' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' ><div class='qx-row' > <div class="qx-background-overlay qx-row-qbn94-background-overlay"></div> <div id="qx-column-tl5vq" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-background-overlay qx-column-tl5vq-background-overlay"></div> <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="beefmaster" class="qx-element qx-element-heading-v2" > <h2> <span> Why Beefmaster? </span> </h2> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-icon-list-b68nc" class="qx-element qx-element-icon-list" > <div class="qx-icon-list-b68nc-wrapper"> <ul class="qx-flex desktop-vertical-layout tablet-vertical-layout phone-vertical-layout vertical-alignDesktop-left vertical-alignTablet-left vertical-alignPhone-left"> <li class="item-0"> <img data-src="http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/media/quixnxt/storage/icons/qxio-android-checkmark-circle.svg" alt="qxio-android-checkmark-circle" class="qx-preserve" qx-svg="" /><span class="qx-icon-text">Profit</span> </li> <li class="item-1"> <img data-src="http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/media/quixnxt/storage/icons/qxio-android-checkmark-circle.svg" alt="qxio-android-checkmark-circle" class="qx-preserve" qx-svg="" /><span class="qx-icon-text">Performance</span> </li> <li class="item-2"> <img data-src="http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/media/quixnxt/storage/icons/qxio-android-checkmark-circle.svg" alt="qxio-android-checkmark-circle" class="qx-preserve" qx-svg="" /><span class="qx-icon-text">Efficiency</span> </li> </ul> <style type="text/css">#qx-icon-list-b68nc li .playIcon img{width:30px;height:30px;} #qx-icon-list-b68nc li i {color: #afa171;font-size: 30px;}#qx-icon-list-b68nc li polygon,#qx-icon-list-b68nc li path {fill: #afa171;}#qx-icon-list-b68nc li svg {width: 30px;}</style> </div> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-gevxo" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2" > <span class="color_15" style="font-size: 12pt;">These are the building blocks on which the Beefmaster breed was created almost 100 years ago in the arid south Texas plains. </span><span class="color_15" style="font-size: 12pt;">Using the Six Essentials of profitable beef production;</span><div class="font_9" style="line-height: 1.875em; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;"><span class="color_15" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Conformation | Weight | Fertility | Disposition | Milk |Hardiness.<br /><br /></span></span></div><div class="font_9" style="line-height: 1.875em; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;"><span class="color_15" style="font-size: 12pt;">The Beefmaster breed is the most cost-effective breed of cattle in the world.</span></div> </div></div> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-image-5gun5" class="qx-element qx-element-image-v2" > <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vc2CojhaTbE' ><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Content/youtube-picture.JPG' alt='Watch on Youtube' class='qx-img-fluid lazyload blur-up' data-sizes='auto' /></a> </div></div> </div> </div> </div><div id="qx-column-i57yu" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-background-overlay qx-column-i57yu-background-overlay"></div> <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-image-csg0x" class="qx-element qx-element-image-v2" > <noscript><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' src='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls.jpg' alt='Why Beefmaster' class='qx-img-fluid' /></noscript><picture><source data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_550.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Content 550w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_460.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Content 460w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_384.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Content 384w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_322.webp&dirs=Siteimages/Content 322w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Why Beefmaster' class='qx-img-fluid lazyload blur-up' type='image/webp'/><img data-width='100' data-height='100' data-optimumx='1.5' data-srcset='http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_550.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Content 550w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_460.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Content 460w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_384.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Content 384w,http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/index.php?quix-image=media/quixnxt/storage/images/Siteimages/Content/BeefmasterBulls_322.jpg&dirs=Siteimages/Content 322w' data-sizes='auto' alt='Why Beefmaster' class='qx-img-fluid lazyload blur-up' data-lowsrc='data:;base64,'/></picture> </div></div><div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-text-ndwbt" class="qx-element qx-element-text-v2" > <p class="font_9" style="line-height: 1.875em; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;"><span class="color_15"><strong><br />Hybrid Vigor (Heterosis) Benefits</strong></span></p><p class="font_9" style="line-height: 1.875em; font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;"><span class="color_15" style="font-size: 12pt;">The hybrid vigor (heterosis) boosts provided by Beefmasters are well known in the American beef industry.&nbsp; Research at Florida State University has shown that the 3-way hybrid cross (Brahman-Hereford-Shorthorn) to combine Bos Indicus with Bos Taurus that was used to develop the foundation Beefmaster breed provides the highest heterosis available from any beef breed in the USA.&nbsp; This heterosis is measured as a percentage of at least 67% for Beefmasters compared to Angus, Limousin, and Charolais at up to 37%.&nbsp; This amounts to a significant weight gain for Beefmaster crossed calves that can mean a herd average increase of 45-50 kg more per calf for the producer at weaning.</span></p> </div></div> </div> </div> </div></div></div></div></section> <div id='services' class='qx-section lazyload lazyload-bg'data-bg=http://www.beefmaster.at/images/Siteimages/Sections/Beefmasters_Services.jpg > <div class="services-background-overlay qx-background-overlay" ></div> <div class="qx-container"> <div id='qx-row-v3dmt' class='qx-row-wrap lazyload' data-bg=http://beefmaster.joomla-5.test/images/Beefmastersin.jpg><div class='qx-row qx-row-align-center' > <div class="qx-background-overlay qx-row-v3dmt-background-overlay"></div> <div id="qx-column-wi4x9" class="qx-column" > <div class="qx-col-wrap lazyload" > <div class="qx-elements-wrap"> <div class="qx-element-wrap"> <div id="qx-call-to-action-w0ljv" class="qx-element qx-element-call-to-action-v2" qx-scrollspy="cls:qx-animation-scale-down;repeat:ture;delay:300ms" > <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_wrapper qx-animation-toggle classic-mode" > <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_content qx-justify-content-start qx-d-flex qx-flex-column"> <div class="qx-element-call-to-action_subtitle"> <